<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1806,2011]" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">
This species was described for a single female labelled “ 
<collectingCountry box="[819,891,1806,1831]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">Brésil</collectingCountry>
, Manuf.[acturé de] Tabac” (
<bibRefCitation author="Kerremans" box="[1221,1424,1806,1831]" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" refString="Kerremans, C. (1896) Buprestides recueillis dans les tabacs par les soins de M. A. Grouvelle II. Sumatra, III. Bresil. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, 65, 138 - 176." type="journal article" year="1896">Kerremans, 1896</bibRefCitation>
). From French Guiane it was recorded by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bily" box="[624,861,1842,1867]" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" refString="Bily, S. &amp; Brule, S. (2013) A study on the genus Agrilaxia of French Guiana (Coleoptera: Buprestidae: Anthaxiini). Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae, 53, 657 - 686." type="journal article" year="2013">Bílý &amp; Brûlé (2013)</bibRefCitation>
from the Kaw region and recently I have studied specimens from the following new localities:
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1806,2011]" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">
“La Désirée, N4°50′42′′ W 52°20′54′′, 
<date box="[635,759,1914,1939]" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" value="2014-08-01">1.viii.2014</date>
, SEAG team leg. // 
<collectingMethod box="[983,1094,1914,1939]" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">Light trap</collectingMethod>
LED bleu” (2 males, NMPC); “Régina—ex larva, 
<date box="[389,484,1950,1975]" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" value="2013-01-04">4.i.2013</date>
, S. Brûlé leg.” (2 females, NMPC, GCCI); “M.gne [Montagne] des Chevaux, 
<date box="[151,273,1986,2011]" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" value="2012-11-25">25.xi.2012</date>
, S. Brûlé leg.” (1 female, GCCI).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,151,213]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,312,151,176]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">Bionomy.</emphasis>
Unknown, but two males were obtained by means of the light trap (see above) which is very unusual in 
<taxonomicName box="[180,318,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Buprestidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
